main_7275581\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104iic1718342502908.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iic1718342502908.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iic1718342502908.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"djz1665702612777\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">udefentity (Default Entity Widget )\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">udefentity</code> widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"djz1665702612777__section_N1001E_N1001B_N10001\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dui1665702869858.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dui1665702869858.html\" title=\"In Form components, it is common to display multiple occurrences of an entity.\">Layout of Repeated Occurrences</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13277e1_d13278e1_d13279e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Logical widget name: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> DefEntity </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Maps to physical widget: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">udefentity</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default definition: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DefEntity=udefentity(backcolor=#deefff)</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Use for: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Entity definition and layout in form\n                        components </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported triggers: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Entity and occurrence-level triggers. For more\n                        information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uqv1665702561461.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uqv1665702561461.html\" title=\"An Entity is an abstract data type that defines a logical data aggregation and its associated default characteristics and behavior. It may be mapped to a table in a DBMS, and is most frequently used to represent the application data, but it can also represent transient data, a collection of controls, or constant data.\">Entity</a> . </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported properties: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> See  <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vbe1665702841258.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vbe1665702841258.html\" title=\"Each widget has an associated set of properties that affect how the data is presented in the user interface. These properties can be set in the usys.ini file, in object definitions, and in script.\">Widget Properties</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"djz1665702612777__section_N100BE_N1001B_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1155835e167\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112103e1_d112104e1_d112105e1\">The default entity widget supports all entity- and field-level widgets, Unifields, labels, area frames, and lines. In the component layout, these elements can be arranged in any way that fits within the boundaries of the first entity occurrence.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"djz1665702612777__section_N100CC_N1001B_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1155835e176\">\n                       \n Configuring the Widget\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112109e1_d112110e1_d112111e1\">You can configure the <code class=\"ph codeph\">udefentity</code> widget by defining the DefEntity logical widget. If it is not defined, the widget follows Windows conventions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112112e1_d112113e1_d112114e1\">It is also possible define logical widgets using specific entity names. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uvn1665702612860.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uvn1665702612860.html\" title=\"Logical widget for styling the default entity widget udefentity in Form components. The properties set are applied to all entities in the application. If DefEntity is not defined, the udefentity widget is transparent and follows Windows conventions.\">DefEntity</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"crw1665702612934.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/crw1665702612934.html\" title=\"Use the [ENTITIES] section of the assignment file to direct individual entities to a path, give the target database table a different name than the name of the entity, or specify the physical file name for database tables for record-level databases.\">[ENTITIES]</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"djz1665702612777__section_N100EB_N1001B_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1155835e211\">\n                       \n                       Widget Properties\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112115e1_d112116e1_d112117e1\">To modify properties that control the border appearance and gradient background color, click the More icon in the entity's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">FRM Widget Properties</span>, then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More</span> button .</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112118e1_d112119e1_d112120e1\">To set the property values at runtime, use the ProcScript commands <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$EntityProperties</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$CurEntProperties</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><div class=\"dataTables_wrapper no-footer\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1_wrapper\"><div class=\"dataTables_filter\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1_filter\"><label>Search:<input aria-controls=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1\" class=\"\" placeholder=\"\" type=\"search\"/></label></div><div class=\"zDocsFilterTableDiv false\"><button aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Filter columns\" class=\"zDocsTopicPageColumnsButton dropdown-toggle\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\">Column<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-filter\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-filter\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu\"><p class=\"dropdown-item\"></p><div class=\"zDocsCheckbox\"><input checked=\"\" data-testid=\"topic-Property-0-0\" id=\"topic-Property-0-0\" name=\"topic-Property-0-0\" type=\"checkbox\"/><label for=\"topic-Property-0-0\">Property</label></div><p class=\"dropdown-item\"></p><div class=\"zDocsCheckbox\"><input checked=\"\" data-testid=\"topic-Technical Property Name-1-0\" id=\"topic-Technical Property Name-1-0\" name=\"topic-Technical Property Name-1-0\" type=\"checkbox\"/><label for=\"topic-Technical Property Name-1-0\">Technical Property Name</label></div></div><div class=\"searchAllTable\"><label aria-hidden=\"false\" class=\"zDocsInputFieldLabel\" for=\"search-all-smart-table\">Filter results...</label><input aria-label=\"Filter results in the table\" class=\"zDocsInputField\" id=\"search-all-smart-table\" placeholder=\"\" type=\"text\" value=\"\"/><button aria-label=\"Submit\" class=\"zDocsInputFieldSearch\" type=\"submit\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-search\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-search\"></use></svg></button><div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"sr-only\">19 rows found</div></div><div><button aria-label=\"Export table to a file\" class=\"zDocsTopicPageTableExportButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-v\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-v\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicPageTableExportMenu\"><button aria-label=\"Export to Excel\" class=\"dropdown-item\" type=\"button\">Export to Excel</button><button aria-label=\"Export to CSV\" class=\"dropdown-item\" type=\"button\">Export to CSV</button></div></div></div><div class=\"dataTables_scroll\" data-testid=\"sticky-header-table\"><div class=\"dataTables_scrollHead\" style=\"overflow: hidden; position: relative; border: 0px; width: 100%;\"><div class=\"dataTables_scrollHeadInner\" style=\"box-sizing: content-box; width: 709px; padding-right: 0px;\"><table class=\"table dataTable no-footer\" count-columns=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 0px; width: 709px;\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Properties of Default Entity Widget (<code class=\"ph codeph\">udefentity</code>)</span></caption><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\"><th aria-controls=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1\" aria-label=\"Property: activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 376.641px;\" tabindex=\"0\">Property</th><th aria-controls=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1\" aria-label=\"Technical Property Name: activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 281.359px;\" tabindex=\"0\">Technical Property Name</th></tr>\n<tr class=\"searchTableDiv\"><td><label aria-hidden=\"false\" class=\"zDocsInputFieldLabel\" for=\"search-Property-0\">Filter</label><input aria-label=\"Filter column\" class=\"zDocsInputField zDocsSearchInTable\" id=\"search-Property-0\" placeholder=\"\" type=\"text\" value=\"\"/><div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"sr-only\">19 rows found</div></td><td><label aria-hidden=\"false\" class=\"zDocsInputFieldLabel\" for=\"search-Technical Property Name-1\">Filter</label><input aria-label=\"Filter column\" class=\"zDocsInputField zDocsSearchInTable\" id=\"search-Technical Property Name-1\" placeholder=\"\" type=\"text\" value=\"\"/><div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"sr-only\">19 rows found</div></td></tr></thead></table></div></div><div class=\"dataTables_scrollBody zDocsScrollBodyDiv\" style=\"position: relative; overflow: auto; width: 100%;\"><table class=\"table dataTable no-footer\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1\"><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"height: 0px;\"><th aria-controls=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1\" aria-label=\"Property: activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 0px; width: 376.641px;\"><div class=\"dataTables_sizing\" style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden;\">Property</div></th><th aria-controls=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1\" aria-label=\"Technical Property Name: activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 0px; width: 281.359px;\"><div class=\"dataTables_sizing\" style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden;\">Technical Property Name</div></th></tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bou1665702610816.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bou1665702610816.html\" title=\"The Attach to Window Border (Attach) widget property attaches the widget (or area frame) to one or more form window borders or split bars at runtime. This allows the element to be resized or moved when the window is resized or a split bar moved.\">Attach to Window Border (attach)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">Attach</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kml1665702613321.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kml1665702613321.html\" title=\"Size of the margin in pixels, on all sides of the widget, when it is attached to at least one window border. The value can be the number of pixels (for example, 2px) or classic.\">Attach Margin (AttachMargin)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">AttachMargin</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cys1665702610904.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cys1665702610904.html\" title=\"The BorderType property is used to display a flat or grooved border around an area frame, grid, or the default entity widget.\">BorderType</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BorderType</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gkz1665702610994.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gkz1665702610994.html\" title=\"The BorderRadius property causes the border of the area frame or entity to have rounded corners. The degree of rounding is determined by the value of the property.\">Border Radius (BorderRadius)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BorderRadius</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n                        Color Properties \n                     </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">ForeColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mux1665702611074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mux1665702611074.html\" title=\"The BorderColor property displays a border of the specified color around the area frame or entity. It is applicable only if the BorderType property is flat.\">Border Color (BorderColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BorderColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lpd1665702587794.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpd1665702587794.html\" title=\"Determines whether the background color is styled with a flat or gradient color.\">Gradient Fill Style (BackColorFill)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackColorFill</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kto1665702611220.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kto1665702611220.html\" title=\"The BackColorStart widget property determines the color used at the start of a gradient background in an area frame for entity. The default is white.\">Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackcolorStart</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mat1665702611295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mat1665702611295.html\" title=\"The GradientStart property defines the edge of the area frame or entity from which to start shading the gradient background color. The shading ends at the opposite side.\">Gradient Start ( GradientStart)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">GradientStart</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ecy1665702611370.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ecy1665702611370.html\" title=\"The DropShadowColor property causes the area frame or entity to be displayed with a 4-pixel shadow of the specified color to the right and bottom of the object.\">Drop Shadow Color ( DropShadowColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">DropShadowColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n                        Background Image Properties \n                     </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scc1665702611448.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scc1665702611448.html\" title=\"Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript.\">Background Image (BackImage)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackImage</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kmv1665702611521.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kmv1665702611521.html\" title=\"This property determines how the data (text or image) is aligned in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Horizontal Alignment (Halign)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">HAlign</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gvp1665702611605.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gvp1665702611605.html\" title=\"This property determines the vertical alignment of data (text or image) in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Vertical Alignment ( Valign)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">VAlign</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dbd1665702611680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dbd1665702611680.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is horizontally scaled; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">Hscale</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sup1665702611757.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sup1665702611757.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is scaled vertically; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Vertical Scaling ( Vscale)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">VScale</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxe1665702611833.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxe1665702611833.html\" title=\"Determines whether the aspect ratio of the image is preserved at all times. True (default) or False.\">Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"djz1665702612777__table_d13280e1_d13281e1_d13282e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">PreserveAspect</span>\n</td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFoot\" style=\"overflow: hidden; border: 0px; width: 100%;\"><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFootInner\"><table class=\"table dataTable no-footer\" count-columns=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;\"><tfoot></tfoot></table></div></div></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"djz1665702612777__section_N10127_N1001B_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1155835e651\">\n                       \n Compatibility\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112130e1_d112131e1_d112132e1\">Compatibility issues can arise when setting the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Border</span> and or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Color</span> in combination with the entity frame properties that can be set in the initialization file.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djz1665702612777__li_d43073e1_d43074e1_d43075e1\">If both the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Border</span> and BorderType properties are set, two borders are displayed.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djz1665702612777__li_d43076e1_d43077e1_d43078e1\">If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Color</span> is set for an area frame or entity, it overrides all properties set in the initialization file, including BorderType and colors.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112133e1_d112134e1_d112135e1\">To prevent these issues in existing components, it is recommended that you use BorderType and its styling properties only for new and modified components, and for new named area frames. If you modify a component to use BorderType for an entity or area frame, it is recommended that you set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Color</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">No</code> and turn <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Border</span> off. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gmd1665702587249.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gmd1665702587249.html\" title=\"This property determines whether a border is displayed around the area frame, entity or occurrence frame, or field. It is set from the context menu in the form canvas.\">Border</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wwg1665702587409.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wwg1665702587409.html\" title=\"Code that identifies a Uniface index color, which represents a combination of background and foreground colors. Applicable only to Form components. Deprecated.\">Index Color</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"djz1665702612777__section_N1016C_N1001B_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1155835e708\">\n                       \n Applies To\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djz1665702612777__p_d112139e1_d112140e1_d112141e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ula1665702613468.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ula1665702613468.html\" title=\"An Entity defines a logical data aggregation. It usually represents a relational database table, but it is possible to define non-database entities for transient data, reusable user interface controls, or other application structures.\">Entities</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rij1704707370362.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Entity Widgets</a><p>In Form and Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the appearance of an entity or occurrence by setting its widget properties, even if there is no entity widget explicitly available.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uvn1665702612860.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DefEntity</a><p>Logical widget for styling the default entity widget udefentity in Form components. The properties set are applied to all entities in the application. If DefEntity is not defined, the udefentity widget is transparent and follows Windows conventions.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/crw1665702612934.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[ENTITIES]</a><p>Use the [ENTITIES] section of the assignment file to direct individual entities to a path, give the target database table a different name than the name of the entity, or specify the physical file name for database tables for record-level databases.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/giw1665702613626.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$CurEntProperties</a><p>Set properties for an inner entity within the current occurrence of its parent entity.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlm1665702687704.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$entityproperties</a><p>Return or set the current representation properties of an entity.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldproperties</a><p>Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/are1665702666827.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$columnsyntax</a><p>Set or return the syntax attributes for the field displayed in a column of a grid or multi-occurrence list.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7275581\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7275581\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget. For more information, see Layout of Repeated Occurrences . Table 1. Widget Overview Logical widget name: DefEntity Maps to physical widget: udefentity Default definition: DefEntity=udefentity(backcolor=#deefff) Use for: Entity definition and layout in form components Supported triggers: Entity and occurrence-level triggers. For more information, see Entity . Supported properties: See Widget Properties . Description The default entity widget supports all entity- and field-level widgets, Unifields, labels, area frames, and lines. In the component layout, these elements can be arranged in any way that fits within the boundaries of the first entity occurrence. Configuring the Widget You can configure the udefentity widget by defining the DefEntity logical widget. If it is not defined, the widget follows Windows conventions. It is also possible define logical widgets using specific entity names. For more information, see DefEntity and [ENTITIES] . Widget Properties To modify properties that control the border appearance and gradient background color, click the More icon in the entity's FRM Widget Properties , then click More button . To set the property values at runtime, use the ProcScript commands $EntityProperties and $CurEntProperties . Search: Column Property Technical Property Name Filter results... 19 rows found Export to Excel Export to CSV Table 2. Widget Properties of Default Entity Widget ( udefentity ) Property Technical Property Name Filter 19 rows found Filter 19 rows found Property Technical Property Name Attach to Window Border (attach) Attach Attach Margin (AttachMargin) AttachMargin BorderType BorderType Border Radius (BorderRadius) BorderRadius Color Properties Background Color (BackColor) BackColor Foreground Color (ForeColor) ForeColor Border Color (BorderColor) BorderColor Gradient Fill Style (BackColorFill) BackColorFill Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart) BackcolorStart Gradient Start ( GradientStart) GradientStart Drop Shadow Color ( DropShadowColor) DropShadowColor Background Image Properties Background Image (BackImage) BackImage Horizontal Alignment (Halign) HAlign Vertical Alignment ( Valign) VAlign Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale) Hscale Vertical Scaling ( Vscale) VScale Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect) PreserveAspect Compatibility Compatibility issues can arise when setting the Border and or Color in combination with the entity frame properties that can be set in the initialization file. If both the Border and BorderType properties are set, two borders are displayed. If the Color is set for an area frame or entity, it overrides all properties set in the initialization file, including BorderType and colors. To prevent these issues in existing components, it is recommended that you use BorderType and its styling properties only for new and modified components, and for new named area frames. If you modify a component to use BorderType for an entity or area frame, it is recommended that you set Color to No and turn Border off. For more information, see Border and Index Color . Applies To Entities Related Links Entity Widgets In Form and Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the appearance of an entity or occurrence by setting its widget properties, even if there is no entity widget explicitly available. DefEntity Logical widget for styling the default entity widget udefentity in Form components. The properties set are applied to all entities in the application. If DefEntity is not defined, the udefentity widget is transparent and follows Windows conventions. [ENTITIES] Use the [ENTITIES] section of the assignment file to direct individual entities to a path, give the target database table a different name than the name of the entity, or specify the physical file name for database tables for record-level databases. $CurEntProperties Set properties for an inner entity within the current occurrence of its parent entity. $entityproperties Return or set the current representation properties of an entity. $fieldproperties Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field. $columnsyntax Set or return the syntax attributes for the field displayed in a column of a grid or multi-occurrence list. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}